{{Infobox company | name = Drummond Tobacco Company | logo = [[Privately held company|Private]] | image = Drummond Company.jpg | caption = Drummond Tobacco Company Building in St. Louis, Missouri | type = | genre = | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = 1873 | founder = | defunct = 1898 | location_city = [[St. Louis, Missouri]] | location_country = [[United States]] | location = | locations = | area_served = | key_people = | industry = | products = | production = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = | footnotes = | intl = }} The '''Drummond Tobacco Company''' was an American [[tobacco]] company in [[St. Louis, Missouri]].<ref name="nationalmuseum">[http://americanhistory.si.edu/collections/search/object/nmah_1361816 Tobacco Shipping Crate], [[National Museum of American History]]</ref>
