'''Jesús Ángel Rojo Pinilla''' (born February 4, 1974, [[Madrid]], Spain) is a Spanish entrepreneur, lawyer, historian, [[political analyst]], writer and journalist. 



== Biography ==
In 1.999 founded the newspaper ''The District'', which later became the leading newspaper of Madrid local information. His long business career and vocation for journalism drives him to create and lead the Communication Group The District and an audiovisual company. 
Director of the radio program "Madrid al Rojo" and candidate for general director of radio TV Madrid (TELEMADRID).

His passion for history led him to investigate, traveling across America and Europe, publishing books on this subject. Speaker about political and historical issues is also a regular contributor to several media communication as an analyst of the current policy.

