{{Japanese name|Matsushita}} <!-- [[File:___.jpg|thumb|right|Yasuo Matsushita]] --> {{nihongo|'''Yasuo Matsushita'''|松下 康雄|Matsushita Yasuo|January 1, 1926 – July 20, 2018}} was a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] businessman, central banker, the 27th Governor of the [[Bank of Japan]] (BOJ) and a Director of the [[Bank for International Settlements]] (BIS).<ref>Bank for International Settlements (BIS), [http://www.bis.org/list/cbspeeches/from_01041997/index.htm Central bankers' speeches - Apr to Jun 1997]</ref>
==Early life== Matsushita was born in [[Hyōgo prefecture]].<ref>Bank of Japan (BOJ), [http://www.boj.or.jp/en/about/outline/history/pre_gov/sousai27.htm/ 27th Governor]</ref> He is a graduate of the University of Tokyo Law School.
==Career== Matsushita was Governor of the Bank of Japan from December 17, 1994 to March 20, 1998,<ref>BOJ, [http://www.boj.or.jp/en/about/outline/history/pre_gov/index.htm/ List of Governors]</ref> having previously served in the hierarchy of the [[Ministry of Finance (Japan)|Ministry of Finance]].<ref>Werner, Richard A. (2003). {{Google books|bHLC7VOc9JoC|''Princes of the Yen: Japan's Central Bankers and the Transformation of the Economy,'' p. 147|page=147}}</ref>
